    <div class="content-panel">
      <h2 class="section-title section-title-glow">Why online career coaching is often better than in-person</h2>
      <p>In-person career coaching is limited by geography — your options are the coaches who happen to be in your city. Online career coaching removes that constraint entirely. You can work with the best coach for your specific industry, level, and target role, regardless of where either of you is located.</p>
      <p>Askia works with professionals across the United States — from tech hubs like San Francisco, Seattle, and New York to mid-market cities across the country — delivering the same structured, outcome-focused coaching remotely that a limited local coaching roster could never provide.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="content-panel">
      <h2 class="section-title section-title-glow">How virtual career coaching works at Askia</h2>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li><strong>Strategy call:</strong> A free 30-minute call to assess your situation, target role, and what's blocking you</li>
        <li><strong>Coaching sessions:</strong> 60-minute video sessions via Zoom or your preferred platform, typically 2–4 per month</li>
        <li><strong>Between-session support:</strong> Email and async review for documents, decisions, and in-flight negotiations</li>
        <li><strong>Structured deliverables:</strong> Each session produces something tangible — a revised resume, a refined story, a negotiation script</li>
        <li><strong>Accountability:</strong> Weekly targets, application tracking, and honest progress reviews</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-tight">
