<section class="section">
  <div class="container faq-stage">
    <div class="faq-header">
      <p class="hero-eyebrow">Common Questions</p>
      <h2 class="section-title section-title-glow">Online career coaching — what to know</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-grid">
      <div class="faq-card">
        <h3>Is online career coaching as effective as in-person?</h3>
        <p>Yes. The research on remote coaching outcomes is consistent with in-person outcomes, and practically speaking, the work of career coaching — resume review, mock interviews, LinkedIn audits, negotiation coaching — is as effective or more effective in a virtual format because you can record sessions, share screens in real time, and access support asynchronously.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-card">
        <h3>What platform does Askia use for virtual coaching sessions?</h3>
        <p>Coaching sessions are conducted via Zoom. Between sessions, support is provided via email and async review. We adapt to what works best for each client.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-card">
        <h3>How often do online coaching sessions happen?</h3>
        <p>Most clients meet 2–4 times per month depending on the coaching package and the phase of the job search. Higher frequency at the start (positioning and resume) and lower frequency during active search (accountability and in-flight support).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-card">
        <h3>Can I get career coaching online if I am in a different time zone?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Askia works across US time zones. Session scheduling is flexible and most clients across EST, CST, MST, and PST find workable session windows.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-card">
        <h3>How much does online career coaching cost?</h3>
        <p>Askia offers tiered coaching packages. Book a free strategy call and we will recommend the right package based on your situation, target role, and timeline.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-card">
        <h3>What is the difference between online career coaching and hiring a resume writer?</h3>
        <p>A resume writer produces a document. Career coaching produces a strategy — resume, LinkedIn, interview preparation, and offer strategy working together as a system. If your only bottleneck is the resume, a resume writer may be sufficient. If you are not getting interviews or are not converting them to offers, you need coaching, not just a rewrite.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

